{"name":"Disciple of Dol Dorn","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":null,"notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Arcane Background (Miracles), Agility or Strength d8+, Faith d8+, Fighting d8+, follower of Dol Dorn"}},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_uunv0c37flf","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Disciple Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"1iGiINf7mSGiVnYW"}
{"name":"Arcane Background (Artificer)","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p><strong>Arcane Skill: </strong>Artifice (Smarts)</p>\n<p><strong>Starting Powers: </strong>2</p>\n<p><strong>Power Points: </strong>15</p>\n<p><strong>Powers:</strong></p>\n<p><strong>Backlash: </strong>A Critical Failure on a magecraft roll cases the magewright a level of Fatigue and all currently active powers are terminated. Optionally you may be called to roll on the Malfunction Backlash Table.</p>\n<h2>Artificers of Eberron</h2>\n<p><em>Magecrafting </em>is simply a renaming of Weird Science to better fit Eberron. Magecraft is the creation of arcane devices as a form of arcane science through an understanding and manipulation of the magic inherent to the world of Eberron. Characters in Eberron with this Arcane Background are referred to as artificers or magewrights.</p>\n<p><em>Magecraft </em>cannot use the <strong>Jury Rig </strong>feature of Weird Science.</p>\n<p>Artificers and magewrights use strange and powerful inventions beyond the normal technological level of the setting. Such creations might be possible due to super fuels, alien discoveries, or the raw intellect of rare super-geniuses who push the boundaries of science.</p>\n<h2>Trappings</h2>\n<p>Trappings (SWADE page 150) for magecraft must always include the item they're associated with. The burst power might manifest through a rod with the head of a dragon shooting a gout of dragon's breath, while \"Marcomanoi's Wondrous Restorative Elixir!\" is a healing potion.</p>\n<p>Inventors must have their devices at hand to activate their powers.</p>\n<h2>Sharing Creations</h2>\n<p>Other characters can't activate the inventor's creations. They might not understand the strange mechanisms required to make it work, the device might not be \"calibrated\" or portioned for other users, or it might just \"fritz out\" for anyone but the creator. While this may seem a bit strange narratively, the \"magic\"-and the Power Points-come from the inventor so he must be the one to activate it.</p>\n<p>Creating devices for others is possible-it just requires an Arcane Device and the Artificer Edge.</p>\n<p>The inventor can use his devices on others, of course, including administering drinks from his magical elixirs or giving them injections of some miraculous super serum he's created. If Dr. Gabriel administers his elixir, for example, he rolls to activate the power normally. If he gives someone the bottle to use later, they'll find it's lost its potency.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Savage Eberron</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":true,"requirements":{"value":"Novice"}},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_ar97r6l0odg","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Background Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"2FFf5p02W5OcYxG5"}
{"name":"Drop!","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>Once per round when a ranged weapon targets an ally within the hero's command radius, the character may order him to drop to the ground. This allows the intended target to fall @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Prone]{prone} out of turn, even if he has acted already, gaining the benefits of @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Cover and Obstacles]{Medium Cover}.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Hellfrost Rassilon Expansion II</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Command, Notice d6+"}},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_n7sal0llwjb","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Leadership Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"2rfppKl5Q4jULRwj"}
{"name":"Disciple of the Undying Court","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":""}},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_uunv0c37flf","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Disciple Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"2uIpUVO3wqJdfM3J"}
{"name":"Necromancer","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>Necromancers are steeped in the lore and rituals of death. They are particularly adept at raising the dead and forcing them to serve their foul requests. While most heroes should avoid such vile sorcery, few can deny its efficiency.</p>\n<p>The benefits of the Necromancer Edge are two-fold. First, the Necromancer may cast the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-powers.Zombie]{Zombie} power at @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Advancement]{Novice} level (rather than its normal @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Advancement]{Veteran} Rank requirement).</p>\n<p>Second, when casting zombie , the Necromancer reduces the Power Point cost to 2/corpse. Additionally, he may double the cost per corpse to increase the Duration to 2d6 hours with a success, 2d6 days with a raise, or permanent with two raises.</p>\n<p>A Necromancer may never have more than twice his @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Spirit} die in permanent undead servants.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Horror Companion</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Arcane Background (Magic or Miracles), Spirit d8+, arcane skill d8+"}},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_geq2hwpuzwp","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Professional Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"3EjM7nZ7MytVIwwT"}
{"name":"True Hero","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>When lesser men fall by the wayside, this hero just keeps soldiering on.</p>\n<p>When the character takes enough wounds to make him Incapacitated, he may make a free @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Soak Rolls]{Soak} roll. Should the roll fail, the hero may spend a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Bennies]{Benny} to make a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Soak Rolls]{Soak} roll as normal. If a character suffers multiple @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Soak Rolls]{wounds} in the same round that take him to Incapacitated, he may make multiple free @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Soak Rolls]{Soak} rolls.</p>\n<p class=\"embedded-example\"><strong>Example: </strong>Fafhrd already has 2 @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Soak Rolls]{wounds}, when two vicious wolves sink their teeth into him, inflicting 2 and 3 @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Soak Rolls]{wounds} respectively. Fafhrd may make two free @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Soak Rolls]{Soak} rolls, one against each attack.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Wild Card, Heroic, Iron Jaw"}},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_1jrlkylls1t","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Combat Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"3ptzNLaZudCb5Oi4"}
{"name":"Reactive Shifting","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>Some shifters can activate their abilities as a reflex. Reactive Shifting allows them to begin shifting as a free action even when it's not their turn.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Savage Eberron</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Shifter (any), Quick"}},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_6tuhxfqx8df","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Racial Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"4xvuFoKy6WMeR0fd"}
{"name":"Monster Hunter","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>The character is completely immune to @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Fear]{Fear} checks from one broad type of creature, such as ghosts, werewolves, vampires, or constructs. If applied to spellcasters, it includes the fear spell as well.</p>\n<p>The Game Master is the final arbiter of whether or not the Edge applies to a particular horror.</p>\n<p>The Edge may be taken multiple times, each applying to a different creature type.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Horror Companion</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Spirit d6+"}},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_geq2hwpuzwp","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Professional Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"656G7ZzgcnCiau56"}
{"name":"Disciple of the Devourer","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":""}},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_uunv0c37flf","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Disciple Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"66A6fONv5sO05gC3"}
{"name":"Siege Breaker","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>This Edge is used only for @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Mass Battles]{Mass Battles}. The hero has a good knowledge of siege warfare and can spot weaknesses in enemy fortifications.</p>\n<p>When he leads the army, the character reduces the Siege Bonus of any fortification his men are attacking by 1 (to a minimum of zero).</p>\n<p>If he makes a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Battle]{Battle} roll at the start of a siege, he can increase the Siege Bonus penalty by an additional -1 for success and -2 with a raise by studying and exploiting specific weaknesses.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Hellfrost Player Guide</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Command, Smarts d8+, Battle d8+"}},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_n7sal0llwjb","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Leadership Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"6J0YLamy6Jz7bJbS"}
