{"name":"Arcane Background (Gifted)","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p><strong>Arcane Skill: </strong>Artifice (Smarts)</p>\n<p><strong>Starting Powers: </strong>2</p>\n<p><strong>Power Points: </strong>15</p>\n<p><strong>Powers:</strong></p>\n<p><strong>Backlash: </strong>A Critical Failure on a magecraft roll cases the magewright a level of Fatigue and all currently active powers are terminated. Optionally you may be called to roll on the Malfunction Backlash Table.</p>\n<h2>Artificers of Eberron</h2>\n<p><em>Magecrafting </em>is simply a renaming of Weird Science to better fit Eberron. Magecraft is the creation of arcane devices as a form of arcane science through an understanding and manipulation of the magic inherent to the world of Eberron. Characters in Eberron with this Arcane Background are referred to as artificers or magewrights.</p>\n<p><em>Magecraft </em>cannot use the <strong>Jury Rig </strong>feature of Weird Science.</p>\n<p>Artificers and magewrights use strange and powerful inventions beyond the normal technological level of the setting. Such creations might be possible due to super fuels, alien discoveries, or the raw intellect of rare super-geniuses who push the boundaries of science.</p>\n<h2>Trappings</h2>\n<p>Trappings (SWADE page 150) for magecraft must always include the item they're associated with. The burst power might manifest through a rod with the head of a dragon shooting a gout of dragon's breath, while \"Marcomanoi's Wondrous Restorative Elixir!\" is a healing potion.</p>\n<p>Inventors must have their devices at hand to activate their powers.</p>\n<h2>Sharing Creations</h2>\n<p>Other characters can't activate the inventor's creations. They might not understand the strange mechanisms required to make it work, the device might not be \"calibrated\" or portioned for other users, or it might just \"fritz out\" for anyone but the creator. While this may seem a bit strange narratively, the \"magic\"-and the Power Points-come from the inventor so he must be the one to activate it.</p>\n<p>Creating devices for others is possible-it just requires an Arcane Device and the Artificer Edge.</p>\n<p>The inventor can use his devices on others, of course, including administering drinks from his magical elixirs or giving them injections of some miraculous super serum he's created. If Dr. Gabriel administers his elixir, for example, he rolls to activate the power normally. If he gives someone the bottle to use later, they'll find it's lost its potency.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Savage Eberron</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":true,"requirements":{"value":"Novice"}},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_ar97r6l0odg","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Background Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"BD5tCsxrf88Yo3CC"}
{"name":"Psiforged Body","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>This warforged's body has trace amounts of psionically resonant deep crystal, providing her with increased psionic power and the ability to store psionic energy in its body. This functions as a mana stone (see Named Miscellaneous Magic in the Fantasy Companion) with 5 @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{Power Points}. A warforged with this edge is sometimes referred to as a psiforged.</p>\n<p><strong>Special:</strong> This Edge must be taken during character creation.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Savage Eberron</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Warforged, Arcane Background (Psionics)"}},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_6tuhxfqx8df","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Racial Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"BVRFHXhJGCn2TFB0"}
{"name":"Ground Fighter","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>The hero does not suffer @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Parry]{Parry} or @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Fighting]{Fighting} roll reductions when @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Prone]{prone}. If engaged in melee against an opponent who is also @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Prone]{prone}, the hero adds +1 to his @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Athletics]{Athletics} (if @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Grappling]{Grappling}) or @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Fighting]{Fighting} rolls.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Savage Eberron</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Agility or Strength d6+"}},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_1jrlkylls1t","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Combat Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"Bnv39qHQKXRhZ08X"}
{"name":"Shieldwall","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>This Edge allows a hero to defend a comrade so long as the hero is using a medium or large shield.</p>\n<p>Attacks against one character adjacent to the hero suffer modifiers based on the hero's shield type. If there are multiple heroes with this Edge adjacent to a character or the target has his own shield, only the best modifier applies. A hero adjacent to multiple allies must declare which one he is protecting at the start of his turn.</p>\n<p>The hero also keeps his shield modifier if he is attacked.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Modified from Hellfrost Player Guide</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Hobgoblin, Block"}},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_6tuhxfqx8df","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Racial Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"Bu4hUnRhZBuMR4GE"}
