{"name":"University Trained","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>You attended one of the prestigious universities in the world. You like to read, and you absorb the information like a sponge. These books can be found in classrooms, in libraries or even in the local coffee shop. Book Learning confers 4 additional skill points on the Character, but these points must be spent on the following: <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Arcana]{Arcana}, @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Battle]{Battle}, @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Common Knowledge]{Common Knowledge}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Cosmology]{Cosmology}, @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Healing]{Healing}, @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Language]{Language}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Lore]{Lore}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Religion]{Religion}, @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Research]{Research} </em>or @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Science]{Science}.</p>\n<p>Because of your interest in books, a character with this Edge gains one additional @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Language]{Language} at a d4.</p>\n<p><strong>Special: </strong>This Edge must be taken during character creation or after actually going to one of the schools of Khorvaire with DM approval.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Savage Eberron</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Smarts d8+"}},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_ar97r6l0odg","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Background Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"K7rpFM3teME9BUTe"}
{"name":"Aristocrat","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>This individual was born into privilege or came into it later in life. She may or may not have money (the Rich or Filthy Rich Edge), but she still walks in the elite social circles of the setting.</p>\n<p>This character will likely be able to place ir' before their last name to denote being a member of the nobility.</p>\n<p>Aristocrats add +2 to @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Persuasion]{Persuasion} when @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Networking]{Networking} with the local elite, captains of industry, nobles, or other aristocrats. They also add +2 to @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Common Knowledge]{Common Knowledge} rolls made to know the etiquette of the upper class, recognize family trees or heraldry, or recall gossip concerning others of their station.</p>\n<p>Typically, a character with this edge has the lowest noble title (his father being one or two steps higher up the social ladder). The character also rules a small manor, small village, or hamlet. Only with the GM's permission may the character begin at a higher social status.</p>\n<p>Further social promotions require family members to move aside (or die) to allow the character to assume a new title, and this should be worked into the campaign.</p>\n<h2>Other Form of \"Nobility\"</h2>\n<p>While the Noble Edge typically covers those born to high station, this is not a firm dictate. The Edge can also be used to represent other character types. A player who wants to use the Noble Edge in an atypical way should always consult with his GM first.</p>\n<p>For instance, a cleric with the Edge may be the head of a small temple. A hero may also be a guildmaster. Normally this should be a legitimate guild, but with the GM's permission, the hero may run a small thieves' guild. A hero may be a guildmaster for a craft guild or perhaps run a way station for one of the dragonmarked houses. The hero must handle labor disputes, raids by the thieves' guild, and so on.</p>\n<p>Although a merchant can be represented by the Rich Edge, one taking the Aristocract Edge might be a well-known merchant or have a sizable business. In return for the +2 Networking bonus, he also has the hassle of balancing the books, negotiating contracts, fighting off competitors, and such like.</p>\n<p>Characters using Artistocract in an alternate way do not gain the titles listed elsewhere. GMs and players should work together to create suitable honorifics.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Modified from Savage Worlds Adventure Edition</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice"}},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_ar97r6l0odg","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Background Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"LAHGXWLbwcdTZkwN"}
{"name":"Master Necromancer","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>Zombies raised by the Necromancer now have an extra die in @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Strength} and one skill of his choice (usually @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Fighting]{Fighting}).</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Horror Companion</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Veteran, Necromancer"}},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_geq2hwpuzwp","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Professional Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"MKQgUjkB4N3CX8Dy"}
{"name":"Improved Sunder","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>Dwarves have an instinctual knowledge of materials. Those with this Edge know just where to strike objects or armored foes to cause the most damage. Any weapon in the hands of a dwarf with this Edge ignores 2 point of @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Armor] (in addition to any @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Armor Piercing (AP)]{AP} value the weapon may already have) on a successful hit. If the dwarf gets a raise on the attack roll, he ignores 4 points of @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Armor]. The Edge applies against all forms of armor, natural or magical.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Fantasy Companion</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Veteran, Sunder"}},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_6tuhxfqx8df","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Racial Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"MOybXMJvoL6c3d6l"}
{"name":"Disciple of the Mockery","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":""}},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_uunv0c37flf","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Disciple Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"NZF418DEFA6MtLtx"}
{"name":"Legendary Storyteller","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>The party gains +1d8 Glory for each raise after the first when using the Variable Glory Awards.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Hellfrost Player Guide</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Heroic, Master Storyteller"}},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_geq2hwpuzwp","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Professional Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"NezB0QwUA1hYdphe"}
{"name":"Blind Fighting","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>Blind fighters have trained long and hard to fight with out being able to see, using smell, sound, disturbances in the surrounding air, etc. You character is able to halves any penalties for @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Illumination]{Illumination}.</p>\n<p>Note this edge does not allow you to see in the dark only to fight at a reduced penalty when you vision is impaired.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Legnds of Steel</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Agility d8+, Notice d8+"}},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_1jrlkylls1t","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Combat Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"Nvf06pJvNzbM1nZc"}
{"name":"Takedown Move","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>When the hero successfully @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Push]{Pushes} an opponent, the opponent must make an @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Athletics]{Athletics} roll at -2 (-4 if the hero got a raise) or be knocked @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Prone]{prone}.</p>\n<p>The wrestler can also chose not to push the opponent 1\" away, but just @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Prone]{prone}.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Savage Eberron</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Wrestler"}},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_1jrlkylls1t","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Combat Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"O4lunLafr5wxud5q"}
{"name":"Siege Mentality","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>This Edge is used only for @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Mass Battles]{Mass Battles}. The character has a strong defensive mentality and understands how to make the most of his fortification and its defenders.</p>\n<p>When he leads the army, he increases the Siege Bonus of any fortification he defends by +1.</p>\n<p>If he makes a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Battle]{Battle} roll at the start of a siege, he can increase this bonus by an additional +1 for success and +2 with a raise by studying and better defending weak areas.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Hellfrost Player Guide</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Command, Smarts d8+, Battle d8+"}},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_n7sal0llwjb","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Leadership Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"O88pNMV6LlzaCihR"}
{"name":"Disciple of Onatar","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":""}},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_uunv0c37flf","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Disciple Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"OEVRZaQOdT8glhwR"}
{"name":"Improved Strong Caster","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>The mage is adept at channeling raw magical essence.</p>\n<p>A mage with this Edge reduces the initial Casting Modifier of all spells by 2, to a minimum of zero. For instance, a spell with a Casting Modifier of &minus;2 only inflicts a &minus;1 penalty to this mage.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Heroic, Strong Caster"}},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_kir10d62ppq","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Power Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"OkRKqgk9TdSAMbLk"}
{"name":"Tinkerer","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>On taking this Edge, the artificer may craft (or modify) an item that adds +1 to the user's relevant trait roll, increases the damage of a weapon by +1, or increases the bonus of armor by +1. No activation roll is required.</p>\n<p>Assuming the artificer is always \"fiddling\" with devices (not locked in prison, for example), and has adequate tools, he may make an Artificer roll at -4 at the end of any session in which he advances. If successful, he adds another +1 to any item of his choice.</p>\n<p>This could be his own wand (bonus to @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Shooting]{Shooting}), the clothing of another (bonus to @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Armor]), or any other item of his choice. The item now adds that bonus to the user's relevant trait or damage roll, or armor rating. No item may have more than a +3 bonus.</p>\n<p><strong>Stacking:</strong> Bonuses from items don't stack, so a bow of accuracy +3 (@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Shooting]{Shooting}) wielded by someone with targeting glasses +3 (@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Shooting]{Shooting}) gets only the highest of the two.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Slipstream Player's Guide</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Crafting d8+, Magecraft d10+"}},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_geq2hwpuzwp","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Professional Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"OwtpdRmNcGV5Wo3P"}
{"name":"Disciple of the Flame","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":""}},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_uunv0c37flf","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Disciple Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"QWccJtITCJjl0gd0"}
{"name":"War Cry","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>Bugbear, Half-orc, and Orc can bellow an ear-splitting, nervewracking war cry that has been known to send lesser foes fleeing from the field.</p>\n<p>When used, the character may make an @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Intimidation]{Intimidation} @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Test]{test} against all targets in an area (as opposed to a single victim as usual). Place the edge of a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Blast Templates]{Large Blast Template} adjacent to the character. Every creature, friend and foe, within the circle must roll against the hero's @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Intimidation]{Intimidation} total.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Hellfrost Player Guide</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Bugbear, Half-orc, or Orc, Intimidation d8+"}},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_6tuhxfqx8df","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Racial Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"Qj31ok29eWwvtqcN"}
{"name":"Born in Battle","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>A good grasp of terrain and tactics, as well as knowledge of military history and enemy forces, can bring a general victory even when his troops are inferior to his enemy&rsquo;s. The character gets +2 to @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Battle]{Battle} rolls. In addition, he gains a +2 bonus to all @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Common Knowledge]{Common Knowledge} rolls concerning military matters.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Smarts d8+, Battle d8+, Command"}},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_n7sal0llwjb","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Leadership Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"RlTe9fVgz6wvdb7C"}
{"name":"Strong Caster","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>The mage is adept at channeling raw magical essence.</p>\n<p>A mage with this Edge reduces the initial Casting Modifier of all spells by 1, to a minimum of zero. For instance, a spell with a Casting Modifier of &minus;2 only inflicts a &minus;1 penalty to this mage.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Arcane Background, arcane skill d10+"}},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_kir10d62ppq","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Power Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"SM7IWEFxQGYD5X8j"}
{"name":"Extra Shifter Ability","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>The adventurer come from a mixed lineage of shifters and has one additional shifter ability. They can manifest this additional ability while shifted as well.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Savage Eberron</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Shifter (any)"}},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_6tuhxfqx8df","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Racial Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"SgSIIJe7eetiftBH"}
{"name":"Familiar","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>The mage has acquired an animal familiar. The creature gained varies with the mage's Rank when he first takes this Edge. Use the Available Familiars table to determine the type of animal a mage can choose.</p>\n<p>The mage and the familiar acquire the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-hindrances.Loyal]{Loyal} Hindrance with regard to each other. The familiar is not a slave, however, and can refuse to follow orders, especially ones which will cause it harm. Unless ordered otherwise, the familiar follows its natural instincts. For example, a cat familiar may stop to chase a mouse, take a quick nap, or sate its curiosity about a small hole, and it's likely to hide during combat.</p>\n<p>The strong bond allows the familiar to resist the effects of beast friend. Each Rank of the mage adds +1 to the creature's Size for the purpose of how many Power Points are needed to control it.</p>\n<p>Both can understand each other's speech. To others, the familiar is simply making animal noises - the mage speaks his normal language.</p>\n<p>The familiar is a Wild Card with respect to wounds and the Wild Die, but has no bennies. The mage may spend his for the familiar, however.</p>\n<p>A mage can dismiss a familiar to gain another if he chooses.</p>\n<p>Each additional time this Edge is taken, the mage can pick one of the powers below. Each power may only be taken once. The mage may take this Edge only once each Rank. Taking it during character creation allows the character to take it again while he's a Novice.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>The mage can transfer wounds and Fatigue levels to or from his familiar as a free action.</li>\n<li>The mage may increase one attribute of his choice which is lower than that of the familiar by one die, to a maximum of d12.</li>\n<li>The mage can use the familiar's senses as if they were his own. This requires concentration. The maximum range for this ability is the mage's Smarts x 100 yards.</li>\n<li>The familiar can use the mage's Combat Edges as its own.</li>\n<li>Any spells the mage casts on himself also affect the familiar. If he casts armor with a raise, both he and his familiar gain +4 Armor for the duration, for example.</li>\n<li>The familiar has 5 Power Points, which the mage may use as if they were his own. They recharge at the same rate as the mage's (usually 1 per hour).</li>\n</ul>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Fantasy Companion</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Arcane Background (Magic), Arcana d8+"}},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_geq2hwpuzwp","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Professional Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"TMWmgimVMrAIyaH0"}
{"name":"Entertainer","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>You character is skilled in ther performing arts: singing, story telling, comedy, acting, slieght of hand, etc. They also adept in speaking before a crowd.</p>\n<p>Pick any two of the following skills: @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Common Knowledge]{Common Knowledge}, Lore, @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Performance]{Performance}, @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Persuasion]{Persuasion}, @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Taunt]{Taunt}, or Traditions and add +1 to the total whenever they're used.</p>\n<p>This Edge may be taken more than once if applied to different skills.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Savage Eberron</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Performance d8+"}},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_geq2hwpuzwp","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Professional Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"TeaA41Aeg6jwh1xE"}
{"name":"Improved Focus","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>Wielding arcane power has its drawbacks, but some people learn to keep their focus even when things don't go right.</p>\n<p>If a character with this Edge is @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Soak Rolls]{Shaken} as a result of failing to invoke a spell, he gets an immediate @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Spirit} roll to recover.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Heroic, Focus"}},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_kir10d62ppq","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Power Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"Tx5ofkgEdkJhsAGm"}
{"name":"Explorer","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>There are two extremes of climate in the world, and this character has survived them both. He gains a +2 to @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Survival]{Survival} rolls. in addition, he adds +2 to resist the effects of heat and cold related enviromental hazards.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Savage Eberron</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Vigor d6+, Survival d8+"}},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_geq2hwpuzwp","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Professional Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"U1X480EWx0syaUN0"}
{"name":"Enchant","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>Enchant allows a character to craft \"enchanted items.\" These are devices which essentially allow the user&mdash;whether he's a spellcaster or not&mdash;to cast whatever power the item is imbued with.</p>\n<p>They require an item that was crafted with a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise}. Each @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{Power Point} stored into the item requires are least 25 galifars of Eberron Dragonshards times the positive of the Casting Modifier of the power put into the item. Each die type for the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{Arcane Skill} roll requires and additional 50 galifars of Eberron Dragonshards up to the a maximum die type of what the caster has at the time of its creation. The crafter has to have the @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-lore.Powers]{Power} available to be able to enchant an item.</p>\n<p>The casting and crafting time is equal to 1 day per 25 galifars of Eberron Dragonshards. At the end the artificer may make an @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{arcane skill} roll at &ndash;4. If he fails on the roll, then all the materials have been used but then&nbsp;</p>\n<p class=\"embedded-example\"><strong>Example: </strong>An artificer with a d10 in Magecraft can enchant a permanent <em>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-powers.Blast]{blast}</em> (&ndash;2 Casting Modifier) wand with a d8 Arcane skill for 200 galfiars and 10 power points an additional 500 galifars. Work on this wand would take 24 days to create.</p>\n<p>Items created through this Edge are referred to as minor artifacts. Items recharge at the standard rate of one power Point per hour. The wielder cannot use his own @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{Power Points}&nbsp;with enchanted items&mdash;they are effectively \"locked.\"</p>\n<p>While a character can add further powers to his own devices, he cannot alter those of others.</p>\n<p>The user can decide which powers he's activating when he makes his arcane skill roll, however. He may also make a single roll for all the powers the device has. If a hero carries a ring enchanted with invisibility and armor, for example, both powers must share its pool of @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{Power Points}, but the wearer can decide whether to activate only one of its powers or both with a single roll.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Fantasy Gear Toolkit</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Arcane Background (Dragonmark of Making, Magic, Magecraft, or Miracles), Arcana d6+"}},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_kir10d62ppq","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Power Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"UcnkRfuvlugPdr4R"}
{"name":"Scamper","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>Halflings are small and quick. Some make great use of this in combat too, scampering about to avoid the blows of larger foes. Opponents of man-size or larger subtract 1 from attack rolls against halflings with this Edge. The benefit only applies when the character is aware the attack is coming, he is unbound and able to move freely, and has no encumbrance penalty.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Fantasy Companion</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Halfling, Agility d8+"}},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_6tuhxfqx8df","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Racial Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"UhBBXegcENijlGaP"}
{"name":"Boarder","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>Many captains instill courage in their men by offering additional rewards to the first man to board an enemy vessel. Few survive to claim their prize. Through skill and luck the character has survived dozens of boarding actions and feels empowered by the adrenaline rush.</p>\n<p>All @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Athletics]{Athletics} rolls involving ropes are made at +2. Anytime he is the first allied character to board an enemy vessel he receives a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Bennies]{Benny}.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: 50 Fathoms</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Athletics d8+, Boating d6+"}},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_geq2hwpuzwp","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Professional Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"V10Ei8E4pawl2yFT"}
{"name":"Arcane Background (Wandslinger)","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p><strong>Arcane Skill: </strong>Wand Magic (Smarts)</p>\n<p><strong>Starting Powers: </strong>3</p>\n<p><strong>Power Points: </strong>15</p>\n<p><strong>Available Powers: </strong><em>Arcane protection, blind, bolt, lower Trait ( not boost Trait), burst, confusion, darksight, detect</em> ( not <em>conceal</em>)<em>, elemental manipulation, entangle, fear, havoc, jet, light/darkness, relief, silence, smite, sound/silence, stun, barrier, blast, curse, dispel, shrink </em>( not <em>growth</em>)<em>, sloth, slumber, telekinesis, whirlwind, accelerate healing, drain power points, glyph, puppet, tempest</em></p>\n<p><strong>Backlash: </strong>A Critical Failure on a Wand Magic roll causes the Wand Adept a level of Fatigue and all currently active powers are terminated. Optionally you may be called to roll on the Wand Magic Backlash table.</p>\n<h2>Rise of the Wand Adept</h2>\n<p>Wandslingers channel arcane firepower energy through the arcane foci of wands, staffs, or rods. Wandslingers came to the fore during the Last War, with Aundair fielding the largest number. Using the arcane focus and channeling arcane power, required less training than other traditional forms of magic. However it allowed a bit more power to be focused using the wand, staff or rod.</p>\n<h2>Increased Power Modifiers</h2>\n<p><strong>Wands:</strong> When the wandslinger uses a wand they are able to use the Range (double range only) or Selective power modifier without spending any additional Power Points. Only one power modifer can be added per casting.</p>\n<p><strong>Rod:</strong> When using a Rod the wandslinger can add the Range (double or triple), Selective, Glow, Hinder, Lingering Damage, or Fatigue power modifier without spending any additional Power Points. Two +1 power modifiers can be cast at once, or one +2 power modifier.</p>\n<p><strong>Staff: </strong>When using a Staff the wandslinger can add the Range (double or triple), Selective, Glow, Hinder, Armor Piercing, Heavy Weapon, Lingering Damage, or Fatigue power modifier without spending any additional Power Points. Any combination of up to +3 power modifiers can be cast at once.</p>\n<h2>Trappings</h2>\n<p>Wand adepts' arcane powers take the form of wand, rods, and staves. Trappings for powers cast should be instilled in one of those devices.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Savage Eberron</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":true,"requirements":{"value":"Novice"}},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_ar97r6l0odg","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Background Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"V6ENC0GYWNSIYqa9"}
{"name":"Help Me!","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>Once per round when a foe moves adjacent to the hero, the threatened character may call for help. One ally within the character&rsquo;s command radius who has not yet acted this turn may try to interrupt as if he were on @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Hold]{Hold}. With a success, the ally must attack the opponent who triggered this Edge.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Command"}},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_n7sal0llwjb","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Leadership Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"V9ys69lTZMvH5aMS"}
