{"name":"Improved Enchant","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>Improved Enchant works the same way as @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Enchant]{Enchant} with one important exception--the power is \"always on\" and no longer requires @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{Power Points} to use (it has infinite points). The cost, however, is 1000 galifars of Eberron Dragonshards per @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{Power Point} required to activate the power.</p>\n<p class=\"embedded-example\"><strong>Example: </strong>Enchanting a sword with Smite would require 2000 galifars of Eberron Dragonshards.</p>\n<p>When the device is created, the creator makes an arcane skill roll. Failure means the Eberron Dragonshards are lost (and at the GM's fiat, the device is destroyed as well--or it could become cursed). A success means the power is activated as usual. A raise means the power forever activates with a raise (if desired by the user).</p>\n<p>Artifacts which are always on (a ring of invisibility, a cloak of stealth, and so on), don't require an arcane skill roll to activate&mdash;but may require an action to \"ready\"&mdash;the ring must be put on, the cloak pulled over the shoulder, etc. Thus a ring of invisibility could always be worn and require no activation roll&mdash;but the wearer would always be invisible.</p>\n<p>Artifacts requiring activation, such as a wand of fireballs, require a suitable skill roll (Shooting for wands, for example). All artifacts created using this Edge are called major artifacts.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Fantasy Gear Toolkit</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Legendary, Enchant"}},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_zp2rc3ab7lk","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Legendary Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"WCDqEikt2JoNaiOA"}
{"name":"Fighting Withdrawl","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>The hero can defend himself even while running away. The character may run while using the Defend maneuver.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Veteran, Agility, Fighting d8"}},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_6tuhxfqx8df","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Racial Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"WWlGbVuCoQPVerrd"}
{"name":"A Few Good Men","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>This Edge is used only for @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Mass Battles]{Mass Battles}. The character knows how to get the best from the troops at his disposal.</p>\n<p>Once the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Mass Battles]{tokens} for each force have been calculated, the character adds one token to his army's total to account for their status.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Hellfrost Player Guide</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Heroic, Inspire, Smarts d8+, Battle d10+"}},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_n7sal0llwjb","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Leadership Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"XZxhwsjMOjOVb9Jt"}
{"name":"Close Fighting","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>This Edge is for skilled knife-fighters, who pride themselves on defeating their foes up close and personal.</p>\n<p>Close fighters move inside most weapons' reach, adding a bonus to their @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Parry]{Parry} equal to the enemy weapon's @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Reach]{Reach} +1 for that particular foe. No bonus is granted if the foe is @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Unarmed Defender]{unarmed} or using a knife or other small weapon.</p>\n<p class=\"embedded-example\"><strong>Example: </strong>A Lhazaar pirate with Close Fighting battles a Lyrandar heir with a cutlass ( @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Reach]{Reach} 0 ). The pirates @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Parry]{Parry} is raised by +1.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Lankhmar, City of Thieves</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Agility d8+, Fighting d8+"}},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_1jrlkylls1t","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Combat Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"Y3YX14eHPRPGOvQi"}
{"name":"Steal Away","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>The hero uses distraction and cover to slip away from his foes.</p>\n<p>The character may make a single @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Stealth]{Stealth} roll as a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Actions]{free action} to avoid attack when @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Withdrawing from Melee]{Withdrawing} from close combat. He suffers a -1 penalty for each adjacent foe. Failure means foes may attack as normal as the adventurer withdraws.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Hellfrost Rassilon Expansion II</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Agility d8+, Stealth d6+"}},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_1jrlkylls1t","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Combat Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"YF5liz6KKC1QiA3K"}
{"name":"Improved Close Fighting","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>Close fighters train to go for vital areas and weak spots for quick and lethal kills. The attacker adds +1 to his @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Fighting]{Fighting} roll equal to his enemy's @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Reach]{Reach} +1.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Lankhmar, City of Thieves</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Close Fighting"}},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_1jrlkylls1t","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Combat Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"YHJxM8T9YpHZj6Ib"}
{"name":"Death before Dishonor","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>This Edge is used only for @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Mass Battles]{Mass Battles}. The character has led his army to many victories, and the men have come to accept retreat as a stain on their honor.</p>\n<p>The character gains +2 to @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Spirit} rolls when rolling for Morale in a Mass Battle.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Hellfrost Player Guide</strong></em></p>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Veteran, Hold the Line, Spirit d8+, Battle d8+"}},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_n7sal0llwjb","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Leadership Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"YJky4zwXl5GUnzzP"}
{"name":"Overload Metabolism","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>The warforged can heal damage at a cost to his other physical attributes by exciting his warforged metabolism. Once per session, he can make a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Vigor} roll to repair damage. On a success, he repairs one @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Soak Rolls]{Wound}. On a raise, he repairs two @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Soak Rolls]{Wounds}. Doing this reduces his @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Strength} and @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Agility} by one die type for 10 minutes.</p>\n<p>If the warforged is @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Soak Rolls]{Incapacitated} and has not yet used this ability, any use of the @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Imbue Item]{Imbue Item} Edge targeted upon him automatically activates this Edge.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Savage Eberron</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Warforged, Agility d8+, Strength d8+"}},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_6tuhxfqx8df","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Racial Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"YPWO7um39Eq1Pkqs"}
{"name":"Bladedancer","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>Bladedancers are elite elven warriors, this Edge is their trademark combat maneuver. Despite the name, they may use weapons.</p>\n<p>When used, an elf spins and dances about, attacking every opponent in his path like a deadly cyclone. On the tabletop, the character makes a running roll and must move that many inches. He may not double back.</p>\n<p>Every target adjacent to the fighter's path, starting with his initial position, is attacked at -2. One small downside to this Edge is that every adjacent target must be attacked&mdash;whether friend or foe. Individual targets may only be attacked once while using this Edge.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Hellfrost Player Guide</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Elf, Agility d8+, Fighting d8+, Two-Fisted"}},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_6tuhxfqx8df","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Racial Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"YpbUuiQlIparSMJz"}
{"name":"Mounted Combatant","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>The character has a knack for getting the best out of his mount.</p>\n<p>They ignore two points of penalties to any @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Riding]{Riding} roll, and may spend @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Bennies]{Bennies} to @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Soak Rolls]{Soak} damage for any mount they are riding or command, using the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Riding]{Riding} skill instead of @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Vigor}. Each success and raise negates a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Soak Rolls]{Wound}.</p>\n<p>Furthermore, he may make a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Riding]{Riding} roll as an @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Actions]{action} to spur his mount to greater speeds. With success, the mount gains +2 Pace for this round. a failure causes the mount to gain no increase to its Pace and it suffers a level of @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Fatigue]{Fatigue} due to the exertion.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Hellfrost Rassilon Expansion II</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Riding d8+"}},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_1jrlkylls1t","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Combat Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"ZRtFRChrGGa2gwHg"}
{"name":"Arcane Background (Druid)","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p><strong>Arcane Skill: </strong>Druidism (Spirit)</p>\n<p><strong>Starting Powers: </strong>3</p>\n<p><strong>Power Points: </strong>10</p>\n<p><strong>Powers: </strong><em>Accelerate healing, animate war tree, arcane protection, banish, barrier, beast friend, becalm, blast, blind, bolt, boost/lowerTrait, burrow, burst, confusion, create food and drink, detect/conceal, elemental manipulation, empathy </em>(animals only)<em>, entangle, enviromental protection, fly, growth </em>(NOT shirnk)<em>, havoc, healing, jet</em><em>, message </em>(animals only)<em>, mind link </em>(animals only)<em>, mind reading </em>(animals only),<em> protection, puppet, relief, resurrection, sentry, shape change, smite, summon beast, tempest, wall walker, zephyr&nbsp;</em></p>\n<p><strong>Backlash:</strong> A Critical Failure on a druidism roll cases the druid a level of Fatigue and all currently active powers are terminated. Optionally you may be called to roll on the Dynamic Backlash Table.</p>\n<p><strong>Activation: </strong>Druids must be able to speak and gesture (they cannot be Bound as per the Savage Worlds core rules) to cast their spells.</p>\n<p><strong>Environments: </strong>Modifiers apply to Druidism rolls based on the environment in which they are using their powers. While druids are typically powerful in natural environments, they suffer penalties while within artificial or worked structures which block the natural magic flowing within the Dragon Between.</p>\n<table class=\"table value-table\"><caption class=\"table-caption\">\n<h2 class=\"table-title\">Druidism Casting Enviroments</h2>\n</caption>\n<thead>\n<tr class=\"table-header-row\">\n<th class=\"table-column-header\" scope=\"col\">Modifier</th>\n<th class=\"table-column-header\" scope=\"col\">Enviroment</th>\n</tr>\n</thead>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td>+1</td>\n<td>In the wild</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>+0</td>\n<td>Rural (farm, worked cavern, mine)</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>-1</td>\n<td>Urban (town or city, artificial structures)<br /><br /></td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<h2>One with Nature</h2>\n<p>The fury of a storm, the gentle strength of the morning sun, the cunning of the fox, the power of the bear&mdash;all these and more are at the druid&rsquo;s command. The druid however, claims no mastery over nature. That claim, she says, is the empty boast of a city dweller. The druid gains her power not by ruling nature but by being at one with it. To trespassers in a druid&rsquo;s sacred grove, and to those who feel her wrath, the distinction is overly fine.</p>\n<p>Druids draw their power from the natural energy fields surrounding the earth, plants, and animals. Although they do manipulate the elemental energy fields, their skill is limited. A druid reveres nature above all. She gains her magical power either from the force of nature itself or from a nature deity. The typical druid pursues a mystic spirituality of transcendent union with nature rather than devoting herself to a divine entity.</p>\n<h2>Trappings</h2>\n<p>Since Druids draw their power from the natural energy fields surrounding the earth, plants, and animals, the trappings of their powers should come from that very natural source. Grasping vines, union with the trees, swarms of insects, birds flocking are all kinds of trappings that should manifest for the powers of Druids.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Savage Eberron</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":true,"requirements":{"value":"Novice"}},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_ar97r6l0odg","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Background Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"ZWNx4PY1jTsnt4IB"}
{"name":"House Scion","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>This individual was born into the privilege of a dragonmarked house or came into it later in life. She may or may not have money (the Rich or Filthy Rich Edge), but she still walks in the elite circles of the dragonmarked houses.</p>\n<p>This character will likely be able to take on the name of their house for a last name, denoting being a scion of the house.</p>\n<p>House scions add +2 to @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Persuasion]{Persuasion} when @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Networking]{Networking} with other house members. They also add +2 to @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Common Knowledge]{Common Knowledge} rolls made to know the information about what is going on within their house, recognize family names or members of their house, or recall gossip concerning others within their house.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Savage Eberron</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Dragonmarked Race"}},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_ar97r6l0odg","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Background Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"ZZKlW5gOrnYcGAYD"}
{"name":"Wrestler","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>The hero is trained in holds, locks, and takedowns. She may roll @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Fighting]{Fighting} instead of @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Athletics]{Athletics} when @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Grappling]{Grappling}. She may also roll @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Strength}+d4 when @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Grappling]{Crushing}. If she already has a damage die from @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Natural Weapons]{Claws}, the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-edges.Martial Artist]{Martial Artist} or @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-edges.Brawler]{Brawler} Edges, etc., increase the damage die by one type instead.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Savage Eberron</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Agility or Strength d6+, Fighting d6+"}},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_1jrlkylls1t","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Combat Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"aA3QCzftu4s9NJTe"}
{"name":"Disciple of Dol Arrah","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>The character treats his character @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Advancement]{Rank} as being one higher for the purposes of taking Combat Edges. He must meet all other requirements as normal.</p>\n<p>In addition, he may cast spells and use @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Fighting]{Fighting} in the same round, treating the combined actions as a single action. Thus, a paladin who @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Movement]{runs}, attacks with his sword, and casts a spell incurs just a &ndash;2 @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Multi-Actions]{multi-action} penalty, not &ndash;4 as normal.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Arcane Background (Miracles), Agility or Strength d8+, Faith d8+, Fighting d8+, follower of Dol Dorn"}},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_uunv0c37flf","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Disciple Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"arxRAas2418G4OMz"}
{"name":"Arcane Background (Divine Magic)","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p><strong>Arcane Skill: </strong>Artifice (Smarts)</p>\n<p><strong>Starting Powers: </strong>2</p>\n<p><strong>Power Points: </strong>15</p>\n<p><strong>Powers:</strong></p>\n<p><strong>Backlash: </strong>A Critical Failure on a magecraft roll cases the magewright a level of Fatigue and all currently active powers are terminated. Optionally you may be called to roll on the Malfunction Backlash Table.</p>\n<h2>Artificers of Eberron</h2>\n<p><em>Magecrafting </em>is simply a renaming of Weird Science to better fit Eberron. Magecraft is the creation of arcane devices as a form of arcane science through an understanding and manipulation of the magic inherent to the world of Eberron. Characters in Eberron with this Arcane Background are referred to as artificers or magewrights.</p>\n<p><em>Magecraft </em>cannot use the <strong>Jury Rig </strong>feature of Weird Science.</p>\n<p>Artificers and magewrights use strange and powerful inventions beyond the normal technological level of the setting. Such creations might be possible due to super fuels, alien discoveries, or the raw intellect of rare super-geniuses who push the boundaries of science.</p>\n<h2>Trappings</h2>\n<p>Trappings (SWADE page 150) for magecraft must always include the item they're associated with. The burst power might manifest through a rod with the head of a dragon shooting a gout of dragon's breath, while \"Marcomanoi's Wondrous Restorative Elixir!\" is a healing potion.</p>\n<p>Inventors must have their devices at hand to activate their powers.</p>\n<h2>Sharing Creations</h2>\n<p>Other characters can't activate the inventor's creations. They might not understand the strange mechanisms required to make it work, the device might not be \"calibrated\" or portioned for other users, or it might just \"fritz out\" for anyone but the creator. While this may seem a bit strange narratively, the \"magic\"-and the Power Points-come from the inventor so he must be the one to activate it.</p>\n<p>Creating devices for others is possible-it just requires an Arcane Device and the Artificer Edge.</p>\n<p>The inventor can use his devices on others, of course, including administering drinks from his magical elixirs or giving them injections of some miraculous super serum he's created. If Dr. Gabriel administers his elixir, for example, he rolls to activate the power normally. If he gives someone the bottle to use later, they'll find it's lost its potency.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Savage Eberron</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":true,"requirements":{"value":"Novice"}},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_ar97r6l0odg","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Background Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"b28xE2KK3wfJhwWQ"}
{"name":"Arcane Background (Psionics)","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p><strong>Arcane Skill: </strong>Artifice (Smarts)</p>\n<p><strong>Starting Powers: </strong>2</p>\n<p><strong>Power Points: </strong>15</p>\n<p><strong>Powers:</strong></p>\n<p><strong>Backlash: </strong>A Critical Failure on a magecraft roll cases the magewright a level of Fatigue and all currently active powers are terminated. Optionally you may be called to roll on the Malfunction Backlash Table.</p>\n<h2>Artificers of Eberron</h2>\n<p><em>Magecrafting </em>is simply a renaming of Weird Science to better fit Eberron. Magecraft is the creation of arcane devices as a form of arcane science through an understanding and manipulation of the magic inherent to the world of Eberron. Characters in Eberron with this Arcane Background are referred to as artificers or magewrights.</p>\n<p><em>Magecraft </em>cannot use the <strong>Jury Rig </strong>feature of Weird Science.</p>\n<p>Artificers and magewrights use strange and powerful inventions beyond the normal technological level of the setting. Such creations might be possible due to super fuels, alien discoveries, or the raw intellect of rare super-geniuses who push the boundaries of science.</p>\n<h2>Trappings</h2>\n<p>Trappings (SWADE page 150) for magecraft must always include the item they're associated with. The burst power might manifest through a rod with the head of a dragon shooting a gout of dragon's breath, while \"Marcomanoi's Wondrous Restorative Elixir!\" is a healing potion.</p>\n<p>Inventors must have their devices at hand to activate their powers.</p>\n<h2>Sharing Creations</h2>\n<p>Other characters can't activate the inventor's creations. They might not understand the strange mechanisms required to make it work, the device might not be \"calibrated\" or portioned for other users, or it might just \"fritz out\" for anyone but the creator. While this may seem a bit strange narratively, the \"magic\"-and the Power Points-come from the inventor so he must be the one to activate it.</p>\n<p>Creating devices for others is possible-it just requires an Arcane Device and the Artificer Edge.</p>\n<p>The inventor can use his devices on others, of course, including administering drinks from his magical elixirs or giving them injections of some miraculous super serum he's created. If Dr. Gabriel administers his elixir, for example, he rolls to activate the power normally. If he gives someone the bottle to use later, they'll find it's lost its potency.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Savage Eberron</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":true,"requirements":{"value":"Novice"}},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_ar97r6l0odg","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Background Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"bBFphyQLlRivUtj6"}
{"name":"Finely  Tuned","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>The artificer has studied under the best masters in his field and has fine tuned his creations to maximum efficiency.</p>\n<p>When creating an <strong>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Devices]{Arcane Device}</strong>, each raise an artificer gets on his activation roll reduces the cost of the power by 1 @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{Power Point}, to a minimum of 1. The Arcane Device must have the full points available to use the power in the first place before rolling. You only need to take this Edge once, not for each Arcane Device.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Slipstream Player's Guide</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Artificer, Smarts d8+, Crafting d8+"}},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_kir10d62ppq","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Power Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"bgDK4gWesyXfWmE2"}
{"name":"True Berserker","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>Some warriors nurture the rage inside them, learning to call upon it almost at will. A True Berserker may make a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Smarts} roll to activate his @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-edges.Berserk]{Berserk} Edge at any time.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Deadlands, Dark Ages</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Berserk, Smarts d6+"}},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_1jrlkylls1t","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Combat Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"btp9jDT8TJBSpFO8"}
{"name":"Arcane Device","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>The artificer is able to arcane devices imbued with mystical arcane power including items such as potions, scrolls, brooches, and other single use temporary objects. Creating more permanent items is takes much more skill and training.</p>\n<p>To create a arcane device, the artificer must know the power he wishes to imbue, have access to a workspace, and basic tools (a tool kit relavant to the device being created). Creating the device requires two hours and eberron dragonshards costing 25 galifars per Casting Modifier of the power being imbued. To make a potion of <em>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-powers.Farsight]{farsight}</em> (&minus;2), for example, requires four hours of preparation and 50 galifars of eberron dragonshards.</p>\n<p>When imbuing powers with variable effects, the exact use must be chosen when the item is created. For example, an artificer creating a potion with <em>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-powers.Boost/Lower Trait]{boost/lower Trait} </em>must choose which @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Trait} is affected at the time of creation. Powers requiring an opposed or attack roll can&rsquo;t be imbued into an arcane device, so <em>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-powers.Boost/Lower Trait]{lower Trait} </em>&nbsp;is not an option and the item boosts by default.</p>\n<p>At the end of the preparation time the artificer makes an @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{arcane skill} roll but Casting Modifiers do not apply. With a success the item is created and may be used by anyone, gaining the benefits of the power imbued. @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{Raises} work as normal increasing the effect of the imbued power. With a failed casting the raw materials are consumed, while a critical failure means the artificer suffers the effects of Backlash for his Arcane Background.</p>\n<p>Powers with a Range other than Touch or Self must be thrown. These devices require an attack roll using the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Athletics]{Athletics} skill and have a Range of 3/6/12. Other items require an action to activate dependent on the specific item (drinking a potion, reading a scroll, applying a salve, rubbing a brooch, etc.) and the item is consumed or loses its power.</p>\n<p>Except for Instant powers, the Duration of the power is 2d6 hours.</p>\n<p>An artificer may only have a number of arcane devices created at one time equal to half his @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Arcana]{Arcana} skill die.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Savage Eberron</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Arcane Background (Dragonmark of Making, Magecraft, Magic, or Miracles), Arcana d8+, arcane skill d8+"}},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_kir10d62ppq","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Power Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"dByenwAcVP0cNIJr"}
{"name":"Bodyguard","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>The hero has learned how to intercept blows meant for others. At the start of his turn the character may nominate one adjacent ally. So long as the ally remains adjacent, he uses the hero&rsquo;s @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Parry]{Parry} in place of his own. This benefit is immediately lost if the parrying character is rendered incapable of parrying a blow.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Heroic, Agility d8, Block, Notice d8"}},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_1jrlkylls1t","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Combat Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"dCXUUnpQ2UxrYKLz"}
{"name":"Spell Finesse","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>The hero is particularly adept with one power.</p>\n<p>This Edge may be chosen once per rank. Each time he picks this Edge he may pick one of the options below and apply it to one power he knows. Each option may only be picked once per individual power, but the same option can be applied to different spells and different options can be given to the same spell. For instance, a mage can take an increased Wild Die and AP 2 for his <em>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-powers.Bolt]{Bolt}&nbsp;</em>spell, but he cannot take AP 2 twice.</p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Arcane:</strong> The hero increases his arcane skill Wild Die by one die type when casting the spell.</li>\n<li><strong>Armor Penetration: </strong>A damaging spell has AP 2. This counts against Armor provided by Arcane Resistance and stacks with any other similar bonus, such as an acid trapping.</li>\n<li><strong>Heavy Weapon: </strong>A damaging spell counts as a Heavy Weapon. It does not gain any AP value.</li>\n<li><strong>Range: </strong>The hero treats his relevant attribute as one step higher for the purpose of determining the spell&rsquo;s Range. Fixed range spells (such as bolt) have their range increased by 2/4/8. Touch and Self spells are unaffected by this ability.</li>\n<li><strong>Selective: </strong>When casting a spell with a template effect, the caster decides who is and isn&rsquo;t affected, to a maximum of half his arcane skill die. For instance, a mage with an arcane skill of d8 can drop a <em>blast </em>over a group of allies and foes and cause no damage to four of his comrades.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Arcane Background (Any), Arcana d8+, arcane skill d8+"}},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_kir10d62ppq","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Power Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"e1tFHze8WJkqbdqz"}
{"name":"Improved Giant Killer","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>The hero may choose to ignore the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Armor] or @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Size and Scale]{Size} of a creature three sizes or more than them. This Edge does not work with @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Area Effect Attacks]{area effect attacks}.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Hellfrost Player Guide</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Heroic, Giant Killer"}},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_1jrlkylls1t","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Combat Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"eEVlpofTxrtAWnp2"}
{"name":"Artificer","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>Artificers with this Edge have the ability to make minor artifacts. Runes or embedded dragonshards are the most common \"trapping\" of this Edge, but such details are left to the individual artificer.</p>\n<p>On taking this @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-lore.Edges]{Edge}, the hero may craft (or modify) an item that adds +1 to the one trait roll, increases the damage of a weapon by +1, or increases the bonus of armor by +1. No activation roll is required.</p>\n<p>Only items that were crafted with a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise} have enough quality to be magically imbued with this kind of power.</p>\n<p>Assuming the artificer is always \"fiddling\" with devices (not locked in a dungeon, for example), has adequate tools, and uses 250 galfiars worth of Eberron Dragonshards, he may make an @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{arcane skill} roll at &ndash;4 at the end of any session in which he advances. If successful, he adds another +1 to any item of his choice.</p>\n<p>This could be his own blade, the cloak of another, or any other item of his choice. The item now adds that bonus to the user's relevant trait or damage roll, or armor rating. No item may have more than a +3 total bonuses (such devices are relics and outside the scope of this ability). The bonuses need not apply to the same trait.</p>\n<p><strong>Stacking:</strong> Bonuses from items don't stack, so a sword +3 (Fighting) wielded by someone with gauntlets +3 (Fighting) gets only the highest of the two.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Fantasy Gear Toolkit</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Arcane Background (Dragonmark of Making, Magecraft, Magic, or Miracles), Arcana d10+, arcane skill d8+"}},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_kir10d62ppq","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Power Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"epEvT8yDvuR0dKnJ"}
{"name":"Shifter Stamina","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>Some shifters can persist with endurance beyond most others. Shifters with this Edge are immune to @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Nonlethal Damage]{nonlethal damage}, and the effects of @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Fatigue]{fatigue} are suppressed. When their shifting ends, any @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Fatigue]{fatigue} effects that would have taken effect during shifting (or that were in effect when shifting began) take effect normally.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Savage Eberron</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Shifter (Any)"}},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_6tuhxfqx8df","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Racial Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"g2LaxbEyoogwYaMc"}
