{"name":"Natural Swimmer","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>Your hero wasn't literally born in the water, but some might believe he was. He takes to it like a fish and can hold his breath longer than most others. Natural swimmers add +2 to their @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Athletics]{Athletics} roll for Swimmings, add +1 to their Pace swimming, and can hold their breath 50% longer than others of their species.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: 50 Fathoms Player Guide</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice"}},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_ar97r6l0odg","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Background Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"gdOcEMv5dSLANPIT"}
{"name":"Skald","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>Skalds are storytellers and poets and artists, able to recounter epic poems, plays, stories, legends, and other information from memory. Skalds learn special techniques for memorizing things he has heard or read, and is well versed in many topics.</p>\n<p>Pick any one of the following skills: @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Common Knowledge]{Common Knowledge}, Lore, @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Performance]{Performance}, or Traditions and add +2 to the total whenever they're used.</p>\n<p>Additionally they may split their skill into two @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.qfnDbhOjzlgycFPJ]{Skill Specializations} as appropiate.</p>\n<p>This Edge may be taken more than once if applied to different skills.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Savage Eberron</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Performance d6+"}},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_geq2hwpuzwp","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Professional Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"iHjcJullVdUPqflo"}
{"name":"Arcane Background (Song Magic)","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p><strong>Arcane Skill: </strong>Song Magic (Smarts)</p>\n<p><strong>Starting Powers: </strong>3</p>\n<p><strong>Power Points: </strong>10</p>\n<p><strong>Powers:</strong> <em>Analyze foe, arcane protection, banish, battle song, beast friend, boost/lower Trait, confusion, deflection, detect/conceal, disguise, dispel, elemental manipulation, false health, fear, gift of battle, illusion, legerdemain, message, puppet, relief,&nbsp; sloth/speed, slumber, sound/silence,&nbsp; speak language, stun, summon beast, ward, warrior's gift, whirlwind</em></p>\n<p><strong>Backlash: </strong>A Critical Failure on a song magic roll cases the skald a level of Fatigue and all currently active powers are terminated. Optionally you may be called to roll on the Dynamic Backlash Table.</p>\n<h2>Masters of Weaving Magic with Song</h2>\n<p>Song mages, more commonly known as bards or skalds, are magicians who work their magic through the power of song. The art is extremely ancient and found among all races, though the most skilled come from among House Phiarlin.</p>\n<p>As well as being spellcasters, bards and skalds are also storytellers and poets, able to recount epic poems and stories from memory. Some play instruments, but most simply use their voice to enthrall their audience. Their talents make them popular guests. Finding a warm place to sleep and a hot meal usually requires nothing more than a tale to entertain the host.</p>\n<p>A skald learns special techniques for memorizing things he has heard or read, and he is well versed in many topics. They have +1 to all Common Knowledge rolls, as well as Research rolls relating to riddles, history, folklore, and such like. Agility is used to play an instrument, bards being conversant in most forms.</p>\n<p>Bards and skalds are also popular with nobility and commoners alike and receive +1 Persuasion rolls.</p>\n<h2>Casting</h2>\n<p>Bards and Skalds must be able to speak to work their magic, but don't need to use their hands. Once the spell is cast, the skald may stop singing, even if the spell is to be Maintained.</p>\n<h2>Trappings</h2>\n<p>The trappings for Song Magic would include singing or playing an instrument. One should consider naming their spells based off the name of a song or poem pointing towards the type of power.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Hellfrost Player Guide</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":true,"requirements":{"value":"Novice"}},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_ar97r6l0odg","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Background Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"jwhdVbkLf1zw0MY5"}
{"name":"Disciple of Olladra","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":""}},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_uunv0c37flf","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Disciple Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"k3S99qEbYaaiwUkA"}
{"name":"Rope Monkey","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>Rope Monkeys are those sailors who may as well have been born in the rigging. They always seem to know just the right rope to cut and pull to swing to some other part of the ship and can ride the lines down to avoid an otherwise nasty fall.</p>\n<p>Rope Monkey has two functions. The first is to allow a character on the exterior of the ship to move to any other exposed part of the ship by swinging from the rigging. This counts as the character&rsquo;s movement and requires a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Athletics]{Athletics} roll. If successful, he moves to any other external area of the ship. He may not move further this action even by \"running.\" With a raise, he can move and gains momentary surprise on any foes, adding +2 to any @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Fighting]{Fighting} attacks and damage rolls for the round. This can also be combined with a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Test]{Test} maneuver.</p>\n<p>Rope Monkeys may also use this ability in forests with tall trees. In that case, the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Athletics]{Athletics} roll is made at &ndash;2 and the character may reposition himself within d10\".</p>\n<p>A foe who wants to take his free attack at a Rope Monkey swinging out of melee must subtract 2 from his roll. The same applies to characters with @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-edges.First Strike]{First Strike}&mdash;they suffer a &ndash;2 penalty to their @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Fighting]{Fighting} roll.</p>\n<p>Rope Monkeys may also make a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Athletics]{Athletics} roll any time they fall from a ship&rsquo;s rigging (and are conscious). Success means they take half the usual @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Falling]{falling} damage by grabbing onto ropes as they tumble. With a raise, the sailor manages to slide down a rope and suffers no damage.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: 50 Fathoms</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Agility d8+, Athletics d10+"}},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_geq2hwpuzwp","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Professional Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"kLUdXaDShPIHtlmR"}
{"name":"Mighty Shot","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>The hero has learned how to use his full strength with a bow. The character calculates damage with his bow as Str+d6, instead of a flat 2d6.</p>\n<p>Mighty shot does not work with crossbows or other ranged weapons&mdash;only with bows and long bows.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Hellfrost Player Guide</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Veteran, Strength d8+, Shooting d10+"}},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_1jrlkylls1t","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Combat Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"lK5KJkxYneLLKTWU"}
{"name":"Knight","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>Knights are chivalric heroes dedicated to a particular cause. All Knights swear holy oaths to their patron, whether it is a god, an order, or a noble, and must answer the call when summoned&mdash;even if it means his certain death.</p>\n<p>Upon acceptance into his order, a knight is gifted with the tools of his trade&mdash;a light warhorse, a lance, chain mail armor, and a medium shield emblazoned with the symbol of his patron.</p>\n<p>In addition to these material rewards, Knights of good causes gain +2 to @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Persuasion]{Persuasion}.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Fantasy Companion</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Spirit d6+, Strength d8+, Vigor d8+, Fighting d8+, Riding d8+"}},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_geq2hwpuzwp","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Professional Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"lasgvMu2CjJXMrx6"}
{"name":"Charge","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>The character knows how to deliver a well-aimed blow at the end of a charge.</p>\n<p>If the hero performs a run action and ends his movement for the round adjacent to an opponent, he may make a single @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Fighting]{Fighting} roll as a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Free Attacks]{free attack} (no @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Multi-Actions]{multi-action} penalty). This cannot be combined with @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-edges.Frenzy]{Frenzy} or @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-edges.Sweep]{Sweep}.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Hellfrost Rassilon Expansion II</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Vigor d8+, Fighting d8+"}},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_1jrlkylls1t","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Combat Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"lzOdZ0MUAUM6zGvc"}
{"name":"Brutal","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>The character with this @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.5r7x1AgEwLUihtZm]{edge} is more dangerous when roughed up. When determining melee damage, he adds his wound level to the roll. A hero with 3 wounds, for instance, adds +3 to his @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Fighting]{Fighting} damage rolls.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Lankhmar, City of Thieves</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Wild Card"}},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_1jrlkylls1t","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Combat Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"m208cpFp9lTrkLE7"}
{"name":"Coordinated Firepower","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>The hero knows how to coordinate missile fire against a single foe.</p>\n<p>Instead of firing separately, all missile troops within the hero's command radius yet to act in the round can fire as a single unit on the hero's action (this counts as their entire action for the round).</p>\n<p>The hero nominates one foe within range of his weapon. He then makes a single @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Athletics]{Athletics} or @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Shooting]{Shooting} roll, as appropriate for his weapon. Each additional missile soldier within the hero's command range (and within range of the target), firing at the same time adds a flat +2 to the attack roll.</p>\n<p>Damage is calculated as normal for the hero's weapon, but he adds +1d6 per raise (not just for the first raise). Coordinating fire in this manner counts as a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Actions]{single action}.</p>\n<p>A hero cannot use Double Shot or @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-edges.Giant Killer]{Giant Killer} in conjunction with this Edge unless all subordinates firing with the hero have those Edges as well.</p>\n<p>Although the soldiers lose their individual attacks, the combined firepower gives a better chance of bringing down a large foe (like a dragon), and unlike separate missile fire, the entire damage roll is applied once against the foe's @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Characters]{Toughness}.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Hellfrost Player Guide</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Veteran, Command, Smarts d6+, Athletics or Shooting d8+"}},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_n7sal0llwjb","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Leadership Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"m7xcyWy98cQNmDPt"}
{"name":"Master Storyteller","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>Tales of brave heroes and epic battles are told across Khorvaire in taverns and around hearths and campfires. Most master storytellers are skalds or bards.</p>\n<p>When using the Variable Glory Awards rules (p. 100), the characters roll d8s instead of a d6s if this hero recounts their deeds.</p>\n<p>In addition, the storyteller is adept at deflecting bad press through carefully chosen words. The party suffers no penalties to Glory if the storyteller rolls a critical failure, treating it as a regular failure.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source; Hellfrost Player Guide</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Smarts d8+, Persuasion d8+"}},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_geq2hwpuzwp","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Professional Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"mQxt6KkPTu2A9kKy"}
{"name":"Symbiont Mastery","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>The adventurer has stronger control over attached symbionts and benefits from increased vitality from the attached symbionts. She gains a +2 bonus to @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Spirit} rolls during any battle of wills between her and the symbiont (see Intelligent Relics in Fantasy Companion). While at least one symbiont is attached, the adventurer also gains a free reroll on @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Soak Rolls]{Soak} rolls.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Savage Eberron</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Spirit d6+"}},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_uyw9lec3zf8","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Weird Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"mTf45dyoslfM5Xol"}
{"name":"Focus","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Wielding arcane power has its drawbacks, but some people learn to keep their focus even when things don't go right.</span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\">If a character with this Edge is @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Soak Rolls]{Shaken} as a result of failing to invoke a spell, he gets an immediate @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Spirit} roll at &ndash;2 to recover.</span></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Arcane Background (Any), Spirit d6+, arcane skill d8+"}},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_kir10d62ppq","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Power Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"nIGKgC1BSodDYxux"}
{"name":"Arcane Background (Dragonmark)","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p><strong>Arcane Skill:</strong> Dragonmark Focus (Spirit)</p>\n<p><strong>Starting Powers: </strong>1</p>\n<p><strong>Power Points: </strong>15</p>\n<p><strong>Available Powers: </strong>Based on dragonmark, see Dragonmark Abilities and Powers below.</p>\n<p><strong>Backlash: </strong>A Critical Failure on a Dragonmark Focus roll causes the Dragonmarked Heir a level of Fatigue and all currently active powers are terminated. Optionally you may be called to roll on the DragonMark Backlash Table.</p>\n<p><strong>Race and Aberrrant Dragonmarks: </strong>This Arcane Background is only available to dragonmarked races. Races with multiple choices can only ever choose to have one kind of dragonmark. Adventurers with an Aberrant Dragonmark cannot select this Arcane Background as well.</p>\n<p><strong>Rank: </strong>Rank requirements for the Power are ignored when taking this edge.</p>\n<p><strong>Skill Bonus:</strong> The mark also grants a +1 bonus to one skill. Each should be chosen from the options listed along side the dragonmark that manifests.</p>\n<h2>Dragonmarked Heir</h2>\n<p>The adventurer has a dragonmark as appropriate to his race, and is considered a dragonmarked heir. The dragonmark grants the a power from those available to the a particular Mark. In addition a bonus to one skill used by heirs of that dragonmark. The dragonmark grants the ability to use dragonmark focus items and a power granted by that specific mark.</p>\n<p>Each time the adventurer selects the New Power or Power Points Edge for this Arcane Background, the dragonmark changes into a larger, more complex pattern and increases in power.</p>\n<h2>Dragonmark Appearance</h2>\n<p>A dragonmark appears on the skin. There are twelve known dragonmarks, each unique in design and power. A dragonmark can appear on any part of the body. One half-elf could have the Mark of Detection across an eye, while another has it in the palm of the hand. Dragonmarks appear with vivid shades of blue and purple and shimmer or even move slightly.</p>\n<h2>Dragonmarks and Backgrounds</h2>\n<p>Dragonmarks are bound to certain bloodlines, and by choosing a mark, you are establishing your character's blood connection to one of the families in the dragonmarked houses. It's up to you to define your relationship to the house. Were you brought up in the house? Or are you independent from it? This is best represented by your background. Consider the following options:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Agent.</strong> You have a close, ongoing relationship with your house. The house agent background is a good choice if you are actively working for the house. Alternately, you could take the noble background to reflect a blood tie to the leaders of the house.</li>\n<li><strong>Independent Scion. </strong>You were raised or trained by the house, but you've kept your independence. This means you don't have many special privileges, but you also don't have responsibilities. Guild artisan is a good choice to reflect basic house training, but you could choose entertainer for the Mark of Shadow, sailor for the Mark of Storms, soldier for the Mark of Sentinel, sage for the Mark of Scribing, and so on.</li>\n<li><strong>Excoriate. </strong>When a dragonmarked heir defies their house, they might be cut off from their family. In the past, your mark would be flayed from your body. Although this mutilation is no longer practiced, such exiles are still called excoriates. If you're an excoriate, consider what you did to deserve this punishment. Were you a criminal? A charlatan? Or perhaps a sage who engaged in forbidden research?</li>\n<li><strong>Foundling. </strong>Your ancestors left the house long ago. You have no ties to the house and may not have known you were connected by blood before you manifested your dragonmark. As an outlander or an urchin, you might know nothing about the houses. As an acolyte or a hermit, you could have put your faith ahead of worldly things, choosing not to pursue a connection with the houses. Whatever you decide, this is an opportunity to talk with your DM about the role you'd like the house to play in a campaign. Do you want them to be your enemy? Would you prefer to avoid them completely? Or do you want to work your way into a position of power in the house, despite being an outsider?</li>\n</ul>\n<h2>Trappings</h2>\n<p>All dragonmark powers, come from the dragonmark themselves and therefore tend to be subtle. Trappings would generally be the dragonmark growing warm to the touch and producing a soft glow. Other types of trappings can be created that should follow along these lines.</p>\n<p><strong>Hands Free:</strong> The bearer of a dragonmark does not need thier hands free to be able to cast their dragonmark power(s).</p>\n<table class=\"table value-table\"><caption class=\"table-caption\">\n<h2 class=\"table-title\">Dragonmark Abilities and Powers</h2>\n</caption>\n<thead>\n<tr class=\"table-header-row\">\n<th class=\"table-column-header\" scope=\"col\">Mark</th>\n<th class=\"table-column-header\" scope=\"col\">Race</th>\n<th class=\"table-column-header\" scope=\"col\">Skill Bonus</th>\n<th class=\"table-column-header\" scope=\"col\">Powers</th>\n</tr>\n</thead>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td>Mark of Detection</td>\n<td>Half-elf</td>\n<td>+1 to Notice or Netowrking (Both Persuasion and Intimidation, see Savage Worlds core rules)</td>\n<td><em>Boost Vigor, darksight, detect/conceal, divination, enviromental protection</em></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Mark of Finding</td>\n<td>Half-orc, human, or orc</td>\n<td>+1 to Notice or Survival</td>\n<td><em>Analyze foe, detect, farsight, insight, object reading</em></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Mark of Handling</td>\n<td>Human</td>\n<td>+1 to Animal Handling or Riding rolls</td>\n<td><em>Beast friend, boost Trait (</em>animals only<em>), empathy (</em>animals only<em>), summon beast</em></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Mark of Healing</td>\n<td>Halfling</td>\n<td>+1 to Healing or Survival rolls</td>\n<td>Accelerate healing, boost Vigor, false health, healing, relief</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Mark of Hospitality</td>\n<td>Halfling</td>\n<td>+1 to Common KNowledge or Persuasion rolls</td>\n<td><em>Create food and drink, dimensional space, empathy (</em>humanoids only<em>), elemental manipulation (</em>air, fire and water only<em>)</em></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Mark of Making</td>\n<td>Human</td>\n<td>+1 to Crafting or Repair rolls</td>\n<td><em>Creation, drain power points (</em>arcane devices only<em>), magecraft, repairing</em></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Mark of Passage</td>\n<td>Human</td>\n<td>+1 to Piloting or Riding rolls</td>\n<td><em>Dimensional space, speed, summon beast (</em>mount only<em>), teleport</em></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Mark of Scribing</td>\n<td>Gnome</td>\n<td>+1 to Lore and Research rolls</td>\n<td><em>Magic mark, message, secret writing, speak language</em></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Mark of Sentinel</td>\n<td>Human</td>\n<td>+1 to Battle, Fighting, or Shooting rolls</td>\n<td><em>Boost Trait, deflection, gift of battle, protection,&nbsp; warrior's gift</em></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Mark of Shadow</td>\n<td>Elf</td>\n<td>+1 to performance or Stealth rolls</td>\n<td><em>Darkness, disguise, illusion, intangibility, legerdem ain</em></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Mark of Storm</td>\n<td>Half-elf</td>\n<td>+1 to Boating or Piloting rolls</td>\n<td><em>Becalm, elemental manipulation (</em>air and water only<em>), tempest, whirlwind, zephyr</em></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Mark of Warding</td>\n<td>Dwarf</td>\n<td>+1 to Notice or Thievery rolls</td>\n<td><em>Arcane protection, barrier glyph, lock/unlock, sentry, ward</em></td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Savage Eberron</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":true,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Dragonmarked Race"}},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_ar97r6l0odg","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Background Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"nnteRCxpEMryQDWo"}
{"name":"Improved Scamper","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>The halfling can move so quickly as to cause multiple opponents to interfere with each other's attacks. Opponents get no @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Ganging Up]{Ganging Up} bonus against the halfling.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Fantasy Companion</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Veteran, Scamper"}},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_6tuhxfqx8df","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Racial Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"owWWF1fP4pQUu31d"}
{"name":"Psicrystal","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>A psicrystal is a fragment of a kalashtar's personality, brought into physical form and a semblance of life. It appears as a crystalline construct about the size of a human hand.</p>\n<p><strong>Psicrystal Personalities: </strong>A psicrystal has its own personality (a fragment of the owner's personality), which gives its owner a bonus on certain types of @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Trait} @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Test]{Tests}, as given on the table below. These special abilities and bonuses apply only when the owner and the psicrystal are within 1 mile of each other.</p>\n<ul>\n<li><em>Bully:</em> +1 bonus on @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Intimidation]{Intimidation} checks</li>\n<li><em>Friendly: </em>+1 bonus on @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Persuasion]{Persuasion} checks</li>\n<li><em>Hero:</em> +1 bonus on @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Vigor} rolls</li>\n<li><em>Nimble:</em> +1 bonus on @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Agility} rolls to interrupt actions</li>\n<li><em>Observant: </em>+1 bonus on @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Notice]{Notice} checks</li>\n<li><em>Resolved:</em> +1 bonus on @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Spirit} rolls</li>\n<li><em>Sage:</em> +1 bonus on @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Lore]{Lore} checks</li>\n<li><em>Single-minded: </em>+1 bonus to @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Psionics]{Psionics} rolls while maintaining powers</li>\n<li><em>Sneaky: </em>+1 bonus on @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Stealth]{Stealth} checks</li>\n<li><em>Sympathetic: </em>+1 bonus on @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Smart} rolls</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Each psicrystal has a distinct personality, chosen by its owner at the time of its creation from among those given on the table. Upon taking this Edge, its owner typically gets a feel for a psicrystal's personality only through occasional impulses, but as the owner increases gains experience, the psicrystal's personality becomes more pronounced.</p>\n<p>As the owner advances, it is not uncommon for a psicrystal to constantly ply its owner with observations and advice, often severely slanted toward the psicrystal's particular worldview. The owner always sees a bit of himself in his psicrystal, even if magnified and therefore distorted.</p>\n<p><strong>Psicrystal Advancement:</strong> At each Rank of the owner, the psicrystal has the following abilities:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><em>Novice:</em> @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Armor] +1; @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Smarts} d4</li>\n<li><em>Seasoned: @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Armor]</em>&nbsp;+2; @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Smarts} d6</li>\n<li><em>Veteran: @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Armor]</em>&nbsp;+3; @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Smarts} d8</li>\n<li><em>Heroic: @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Armor]</em>&nbsp;+4; @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Smarts} d10</li>\n<li><em>Legendary: @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Armor]</em>&nbsp;+5; @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Smarts} d12</li>\n</ul>\n<p>A psicrystal can speak one language of its owner's choice (so long as it is a language the owner knows). A psicrystal can understand all other languages known by its owner, but cannot speak them.</p>\n<p>Because of the telepathic link between a psicrystal and its owner, the owner has the same connection to an item or place that the psicrystal does. For instance, if his psicrystal has seen a room, the owner can teleport into that room as if he has seen it too, negating the -4 penalty for the destination being an unknown area; the -2 penalty for not being able to see it presently might still apply.</p>\n<p>The psicrystal is a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Wild Cards and Extras]{Wild Cards} with respect to Wounds and the Wild Die, but has no Prophecy Shards. The owner may spend his for the psicrystal, however.</p>\n<p>Each additional time this Edge is taken, the psion can pick one of the powers below. Each power may only be taken once. The psion may take this Edge only once each Rank. Taking it during character creation allows the psion to take it again while he's a Novice.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>The psicrystal gains @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-edges.Arcane Resistance]{Arcane Resistance} against psionics.</li>\n<li>The psion can transfer @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Damage Effects]{Wounds} and @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Fatigue]{Fatigue} levels to or from his psicrystal as a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Actions]{free actions}.</li>\n<li>The psion can use the psicrystal's senses as if they were his own. This requires concentration. The maximum range for this ability is the psion's @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Smarts} x 100 yards.</li>\n<li>Whenever the psicrystal is adjacent to or in the possession of its owner, the owner has the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-edges.Alertness]{Alertness} Edge.</li>\n<li>Any powers the psion manifests on himself also affect the psicrystal. If he manifests armor with a raise, both he and his psicrystal gain +4 @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Armor] for the duration, for example.</li>\n<li>The psicrystal has 5 @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{Power Points}, which the psion may use as if they were his own. They recharge at the same rate as the psion's (usually 1 per hour).</li>\n<li>The psicrystal can act as a conduit for the psion's powers by delivering touch powers manifested by its owner. The owner and the psicrystal must be in contact at the time the power is manifested. The power must be delivered before the owner can manifest another power. At @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Advancement]{Legendary} Rank, the owner can manifest the power through the psicrystal to a distance of up to 1 mile.</li>\n<li>At @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Advancement]{Seasoned} Rank or above, the owner, as a standard action, can will his psicrystal to fly with @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Movement]{Pace} 6. The effect lasts for one day (or until the owner dismisses it, at which point the psicrystal drifts gently to the ground).</li>\n</ul>\n<p>If the psicrystal is destroyed, the character must take this Edge again to create a new psicrystal. However, the previous acquisitions of this Edge to add to its abilities are applied to the new psicrystal.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Savage Eberron</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Kalashtar, Arcane Background (Psionics), Smarts d8+"}},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_6tuhxfqx8df","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Racial Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"pMC7btatUJJqEsHb"}
{"name":"Attune Arcane Weapon","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>Some artificers become adept at eking every advantage out of an arcane device's enchanted qualities.</p>\n<p>When wielding a weapon that is an @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Devices]{arcane device}, artificers with this Edge gain a +1 bonus on attack and damage rolls. They must spend 24 hours with a newly acquired magic weapon before they can gain this benefit when wielding it.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Savage Eberron</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Artificer"}},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_kir10d62ppq","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Power Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"qWvx1AMZDk2PFjSK"}
