{"name":"Sunder","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>Dwarves have an instinctual knowledge of materials. Those with this Edge know just where to strike objects or armored foes to cause the most damage. Any weapon in the hands of a dwarf with this Edge ignores 1 point of @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Armor]{armor} (in addition to any @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Armor Piercing (AP)]{AP} value the weapon may already have) on a successful hit. The Edge applies against all forms of armor, natural or magical.&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Fantasy Companion</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Dwarf"}},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_6tuhxfqx8df","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Racial Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"rJNCDSHpZ3Ek9F2B"}
{"name":"Improved Primal Fury","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>With sufficient willpower, a hero who has learned to trigger his rage can restrain it as well. Improved Primal Fury allows the hero to ignore the -2 penalty to end his rage, and on a Critical Failure, he will not hit an ally while @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-edges.Berserk]{Berserk} (though he may still hit the wrong opponent or miss).</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Fantasy Companion</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Veteran, Primal Fury, Spirit d8+"}},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_6tuhxfqx8df","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Racial Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"sDtetY2vIyPxsGls"}
