{"name":"Holy Adept","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>Adepts are holy warriors who have trained themselves to be living weapons. Some do so to be ultimate warriors; others do it in the service of a cause or deity.</p>\n<p>Their unarmed attacks do @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Strength}+d4 damage, and they are always considered armed for purposes of the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Unarmed Defender]{Unarmed Defender} rule.</p>\n<p>In addition, upon taking this Edge and at each new Rank, they may choose to change the trappings of one of the following powers to work only on themselves but be activated as a free action: @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-powers.Boost/Lower Trait]{Boost/Lower Trait}, @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-powers.Deflection]{Deflection}, @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-powers.Healing]{Healing}, @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-powers.Smite]{Smite}, or @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-powers.Sloth/Speed]{Speed}. The Adept must have the power to begin with, and this does not allow him to activate more than one power in a round.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Fantasy Companion</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Arcane Background (Miracles), Faith d8+, Fighting d8+"}},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_geq2hwpuzwp","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Professional Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"wYgaxWUpAIsvFjoj"}
{"name":"Arcane Background (Aberrant Dragonmark)","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p><strong>Arcane Skill:</strong> Dragonmark Focus</p>\n<p><strong>Starting Powers: </strong>1</p>\n<p><strong>Power Points: </strong>15</p>\n<p><strong>Available Powers: </strong><em>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-powers.Barrier]{Barrier}, @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-powers.Blast]{Blast}, @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-powers.Blind]{Blind}, @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-powers.Bolt]{Bolt}, @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-powers.Boost/Lower Trait]{Boost/Lower Trait}, @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-powers.DjrMNL96JvjwS8uC]{Burrow}, @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-powers.Fr956ZstTkWTDR6p]{Burst}, @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-powers.129VEYnmJFIhV6U4]{Confusion}, curse, @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-powers.IolqQaMsF06ABFAC]{Damage Field}, @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-powers.jNbTbrOAKFDgVPOq]{Light / Darkness (Darkness only)}, @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-powers.AT8MC6UZ2ycKMHBe]{Darksight}<em>, @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-powers.Dispel]{Dispel}, @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-powers.z8MkfaFMxq4g89az]{Drain Power Points}, elemental form, @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-powers.kLfXd5xIIJdkCNZC]{Elemental Manipulation (fire only)}, @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-powers.yFM0x9h5mPjy6aPn]{Entangle}, @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-powers.dgJK0KgZ1dxRBpPU]{Fear}, grave speak, @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-powers.L5A38yXaNM0QdjPV]{Havoc}, jet, leaping, @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-powers.4d2eB87lpMNatFik]{Mind Wipe}, @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-powers.Puppet]{Puppet}, @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-powers.kWYcqj1FtZFUOTo1]{Growth/Shrink}, silence, @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-powers.Sloth/Speed]{Sloth/Speed}, @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-powers.EkwXiOTMt9c9s3JE]{Slumber}, @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-powers.Smite]{Smite}, summon demon, summon elemental, @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-powers.TXEGV10mCa1u5w5c]{Telekinesis}, tempest </em>(create storm only)<em>, @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-powers.GaPBXGuoBOVDmIEf]{Warrior's Gift}, @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-powers.Zombie]{Zombie}</em></em></p>\n<p><strong>Backlash: </strong>A Critical Failure on a Dragonmark Focus roll cases the Aberrant marked a level of Fatigue and all currently active powers are terminated. Optionally you may be called to roll on the DragonMark Backlash Table.</p>\n<p><strong>Race and House Dragonmarks:</strong> Adventurers with the Arcane Background (Dragonmark) cannot select this Arcane Background as well.</p>\n<p><strong>Hands Free:</strong> The bearer of a dragonmark does not need thier hands free to be able to cast their dragonmark power(s).</p>\n<p><strong>Special:</strong> A character whose mark is clearly visible must deal with the consequences of carrying it. Characters with this Edge also have the Outsider (Major) Hindrance, but do not gain additional points.</p>\n<p>Each time the adventurer selects the New Power or Power Points Edge for this Arcane Background, her dragonmark changes into a larger, more complex pattern and increases in power.</p>\n<h2>Dragonmark Appearance</h2>\n<p>A dragonmark appears on the skin and can appear on any part of the body. The design of the mark is a sinuous pattern of lines, often with a vaguely draconic shape. No two aberrant marks are identical. Certain standard patterns provide hints as to the powers they grant, but two aberrant marks that grant the same power can be wildly divergent in appearance. Aberrant dragonmarks come in a wide range of colors, including oily black, blood red, and vivid green. The flesh around an aberrant dragonmark is often covered with welts and boils, and marks related to fire sometimes leave scars or burns on the skin.</p>\n<h2>Aberrant History</h2>\n<p>It usually takes time for a character to learn to control an aberrant mark, and in time, people might be hurt by it. This factor has led to the general superstition that people with aberrant dragonmarks are dangerous.</p>\n<p>Aberrant marks are feared for another reason, too. Long ago, aberrant marks were more common and some held great powers. Aberrant leader Halas Tarkanan could devastate cities with powerful earthquakes. The Lady of the Plague wielded disease and commanded hordes of vermin. The dragonmarked houses united in an inquisition called the War of the Mark. Some say this was a persecution of innocents, but most feared the aberrants and stood by as the houses hunted them down. Following the War of the Mark, aberrant dragonmarks were few in number and relatively weak. But since the Mourning, aberrant marks have been appearing in greater numbers.</p>\n<h2>Trappings</h2>\n<p>All dragonmark powers, come from the dragonmark themselves. All Aberrant Dragonmarks manifest powers that are destructive and often have that same impact on the user. So trappings might be the dragonmark growing warm to the touch and producing a soft glow. A bolt of fire, might lightly blister the hero around the the mark itself. A boost Trait (Strength) might see the place of the dragonmark on the hero grow in size. Darksight might show black circles around the hero's eyes when active.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Savage Eberron</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice"}},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_ar97r6l0odg","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Background Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"wx6oqCl3mHHRR1bj"}
{"name":"Lunge","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>A lunge allows a swordsman to extend the reach of his weapon. The character gains +1 @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Reach]{Reach} to his weapon. He may not use this Edge with @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-edges.First Strike]{First Strike}, @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-edges.Frenzy]{Frenzy}, or @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-edges.Sweep]{Sweep}.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Lankhmar, City of Thieves</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":true,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Fighting d8+"}},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_1jrlkylls1t","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Combat Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"xGaUKzS7gOgJlrH1"}
{"name":"Sucker Punch","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>The character doesn't know the meaning of the words \"fair fight.\" If he succeeds in a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Test]{Test} against an adjacent opponent, the character receives a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Free Attacks]{free attack}. This attack does not incur a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Multi-Actions]{multi-action penalty}.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Slipstream Player's Guide</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, First Strike, Agility d6+, Fighting d8+"}},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_1jrlkylls1t","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Combat Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"xJHco8TCxvXLvVhk"}
